# Guidelines

## No Inventions

Only make changes that are explicitly requested. Do not add unrequested features, refactors, or improvements.

## Preserve Existing Code

Do not remove unrelated code, functionalities, or comments without explicit reason. Pay attention to preserving existing structures.

## No CODEMAP

Never generate architecture maps, codemap files, or similar high-maintenance documentation that duplicates what is already in cursor rules, docstrings, and README. These files go stale fast and create maintenance burden.
